description = "List which AI CLIs are installed and available for /peer-ai consultation"
prompt = """
Check which AI CLIs are installed on this machine and present a table to the user.

# Detection

{{#if_target codex}}
Codex:  !{which codex 2>/dev/null || echo "(not installed)"}
{{/if_target}}
{{#if_target claude}}
Claude: !{which claude 2>/dev/null || echo "(not installed)"}
{{/if_target}}

# Present

Show the user a short table:
{{#each_target}}
  - {{target_label}}: <path or "not installed">
{{/each_target}}

Then remind them of usage:
{{#each_target}}
  /peer-ai:{{target_key}} <question>   — ask {{target_label}}
{{/each_target}}

If ALL peer CLIs are missing, suggest they install at least one before consulting. If Gemini is the only AI available, note that `/peer-ai` is most useful when there's a peer to consult with.

Configured at install time by peer-ai v{{version}}.
"""
